'''Accessary''', ''<code>[[adjective (part of speech)|adjective]]</code>''

[[Accompanying]], as a subordinate; additional; [[accessory]]; esp., uniting in, or [[contributing]] to, a crime, but not as chief [[actor]]. See [[Accessory]].

<code>To both their deaths thou shalt be ''accessary''. ''[[Shakespeare (source)|Shakespeare]].''</code>

<code>Amongst many secondary and ''accessary'' causes that support monarchy, these are not of least reckoning. ''[[Milton (source)|Milton]].''</code>
